2026-04-20 11:54:52 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['diode (load module)'] hypothesis_explanation='The relay receives proper control voltage and is physically in the closed position, yet there is no voltage across the lamp or lamp indicator despite the relay being closed. This indicates the relay is functioning, and the upstream power is present (as verified by the power supply indicator LED). The persistent symptom is that neither lamp receives voltage when expected, despite the relay being closed. The most probable cause is that the diode in the load module is faulty: it may be open, blocking current even when the polarity is correct. This explains why both lamps are off (0V) during relay closure and why the cyclic lamp behavior is occurring (the relay cycles, but the diode is not passing current, possibly due to damage or a highly intermittent open fault in the diode).'
